    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="upa.00061.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">431 Stevens Street</name>
                    <name type="place">Camden New Jersey<ptr target="upa.00061_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1879-02-21" rend="right">Feb 21</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Bee</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Your letter <choice><abbr>rec'd</abbr><expan>received</expan></choice>, &#38; we all read it with interest<ptr target="upa.00061_n2"/>&#8212;my sister sends love&#8212;We are all about the same&#8212;I am continuing well for me&#8212;To day is very clear, but cold &#38; windy&#8212;I have been out some two hours enjoying it&#8212;cross'd the 
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="upa.00061.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                
                river&#8212;The Staffords, (with the exception of Mr H<ptr target="upa.00061_n3"/> who has a spell) are well as usual&#8212;Harry comes up to see me occasionally<ptr target="upa.00061_n4"/>&#8212;</p>
            
            <p>&#8212;A note from your mother yesterday forwarding the enclosed letter of Rossetti's which she wished me to post to you&#8212;So far my rheumatic (neuralgic) attack keeps off&#8212;But I am not out of the woods till April sets in&#8212;</p>
       
            <closer>
                <signed>W.W.</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.02159.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.02159.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
